            "id": "https://korus-projects.github.io/blog/my-journey-into-java-and-korus",
            "content_html": "<p>Hello everyone! I‚Äôm <strong>Vinit Shinde</strong> from <strong>Pune</strong>, currently in my <strong>final year at PICT</strong>. This blog is a small part of my story as a developer and the journey that eventually led to the creation of the <strong>Korus Java Framework</strong>.</p>\n<h2 class=\"anchor anchorTargetHideOnScrollNavbar_vjPI\" id=\"how-everything-started\">How Everything Started<a href=\"https://korus-projects.github.io/blog/my-journey-into-java-and-korus#how-everything-started\" class=\"hash-link\" aria-label=\"Direct link to How Everything Started\" title=\"Direct link to How Everything Started\" translate=\"no\">‚Äã</a></h2>\n<p>Right after completing my 12th, I directly jumped into programming. I didn‚Äôt explore multiple languages‚ÄîI started straight with <strong>Java</strong>, and that became my world.</p>\n<p>The biggest influence behind my entry into programming was <strong>my cousins</strong>. They guided me, motivated me, and pushed me toward Java when I didn‚Äôt even fully understand what programming actually was.</p>\n<p>Looking back, choosing Java as my first language was one of the best decisions I‚Äôve ever made.</p>\n<h2 class=\"anchor anchorTargetHideOnScrollNavbar_vjPI\" id=\"growing-with-java\">Growing with Java<a href=\"https://korus-projects.github.io/blog/my-journey-into-java-and-korus#growing-with-java\" class=\"hash-link\" aria-label=\"Direct link to Growing with Java\" title=\"Direct link to Growing with Java\" translate=\"no\">‚Äã</a></h2>\n<p>As I got deeper into the language, I began to explore:</p>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"\">Modern Java frameworks</li>\n<li class=\"\">Real-world projects</li>\n<li class=\"\">End-to-end development</li>\n<li class=\"\">Deployment pipelines</li>\n</ul>\n<p>I still remember the moment when I built and deployed a complete project using a modern framework‚Äîthat‚Äôs when I felt <strong>truly confident</strong>. That‚Äôs when I realized:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>\"Yes, I can build real engineering systems.\"</strong></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Since then, I‚Äôve built over <strong>50+ public GitHub repositories</strong>, constantly improving my skills and learning everything from the ground up.</p>\n<h2 class=\"anchor anchorTargetHideOnScrollNavbar_vjPI\" id=\"why-i-created-korus\">Why I Created Korus<a href=\"https://korus-projects.github.io/blog/my-journey-into-java-and-korus#why-i-created-korus\" class=\"hash-link\" aria-label=\"Direct link to Why I Created Korus\" title=\"Direct link to Why I Created Korus\" translate=\"no\">‚Äã</a></h2>\n<p>India has a massive developer ecosystem, especially around Java, but one thing always felt missing:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>We didn‚Äôt have our own Java framework.</strong></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>That thought stayed with me. And one day, I decided:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>\"If something doesn‚Äôt exist, I will build it myself.\"</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>That‚Äôs how <strong>Korus</strong> started.</p>\n<p>Korus is my attempt to bring something fresh, fast, and developer-friendly to the Java world, built with a strong vision and the belief that Indian developers can create world-class open-source tools.</p>\n<h2 class=\"anchor anchorTargetHideOnScrollNavbar_vjPI\" id=\"vision-for-the-future\">Vision for the Future<a href=\"https://korus-projects.github.io/blog/my-journey-into-java-and-korus#vision-for-the-future\" class=\"hash-link\" aria-label=\"Direct link to Vision for the Future\" title=\"Direct link to Vision for the Future\" translate=\"no\">‚Äã</a></h2>\n<p>My dream is simple:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>In the next 5 years, Korus should become one of the top Java frameworks in the world.</strong></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Not just another project‚Äîbut something developers love, trust, and use confidently.</p>\n<p>This is just the beginning.</p>\n<h2 class=\"anchor anchorTargetHideOnScrollNavbar_vjPI\" id=\"final-words\">Final Words<a href=\"https://korus-projects.github.io/blog/my-journey-into-java-and-korus#final-words\" class=\"hash-link\" aria-label=\"Direct link to Final Words\" title=\"Direct link to Final Words\" translate=\"no\">‚Äã</a></h2>\n<p>If you're reading this:</p>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"\">Start early</li>\n<li class=\"\">Learn consistently</li>\n<li class=\"\">Build fearlessly</li>\n</ul>\n<p>You don‚Äôt need a perfect background or perfect conditions. You just need passion, discipline, and the courage to start.</p>\n<p>Thank you for reading. This journey has shaped me as a developer, and Korus is the biggest step of that journey. The best part is still ahead.</p>",
